WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.199
Re-sync by gzeds

2
00:02:40.332 --> 00:02:41.660
Zeus.

3
00:02:46.442 --> 00:02:47.771
Poseidon.

4
00:02:48.457 --> 00:02:49.775
It's been many years.

5
00:02:53.962 --> 00:02:55.365
What do you see?

6
00:02:59.831 --> 00:03:01.102
Thunderclouds.

7
00:03:03.552 --> 00:03:05.132
But no lightning.

8
00:03:07.942 --> 00:03:09.279
Stolen.

9
00:03:12.554 --> 00:03:13.832
What?

10
00:03:13.832 --> 00:03:15.179
Do you think I took it?

11
00:03:16.504 --> 00:03:18.385
Omnipotence has blinded. brother.

12
00:03:19.044 --> 00:03:21.157
We are forbidden from stealing
each other's powers.

13
00:03:23.346 --> 00:03:24.771
But our children aren't.

14
00:03:26.266 --> 00:03:27.668
You're accusing my son?

15
00:03:29.257 --> 00:03:31.309
I haven't seen him
since he was a baby.

16
00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:34.129
He doesn't know me or even know
who he is. because of you.

17
00:03:34.402 --> 00:03:35.941
If your son is the thief.

18
00:03:37.028 --> 00:03:39.138
I will send him to the
depths of Tartarus.

19
00:03:40.342 --> 00:03:44.458
If you touch him. you will
have the fight of your life.

20
00:03:48.474 --> 00:03:50.339
He must return the bolt to me.

21
00:03:51.230 --> 00:03:55.532
in 14 days. by midnight
in the summer solstice.

22
00:04:02.465 --> 00:04:04.126
Or there will be war.

23
00:05:39.895 --> 00:05:41.205
And he's alive.

24
00:05:44.722 --> 00:05:49.285
Percy Jackson is a beast.
You're a beast. man.

25
00:05:50.509 --> 00:05:52.570
- How long was it?
- Seven minutes.

26
00:05:52.599 --> 00:05:54.440
- Seven minutes?
- Uh hmmm.

27
00:05:55.195 --> 00:05:57.831
That's crazy. man. that's
ridiculous. How do you do it?

28
00:05:58.122 --> 00:05:59.390
I just like being in the water.

29
00:06:01.011 --> 00:06:02.491
It's the only place
I can think.

30
00:06:15.943 --> 00:06:18.089
I wish I could spend all day in
the water instead of this place.

31
00:06:19.077 --> 00:06:20.657
Right. like high school without the musical.

32
00:06:22.036 --> 00:06:23.486
Every day is the same thing.

33
00:06:32.689 --> 00:06:35.092
Good morning. I'm Ms. Dodds.

34
00:06:35.266 --> 00:06:37.108
The substitute English teacher.

35
00:06:37.870 --> 00:06:39.443
Would someone please
explain what Shakespeare

36
00:06:39.928 --> 00:06:42.349
was trying to convey
in this line from Othello?

37
00:06:46.031 --> 00:06:47.358
Percy Jackson.

38
00:06:52.083 --> 00:06:53.718
Well...

39
00:07:01.349 --> 00:07:02.939
I'm sorry. I don't know.

40
00:07:05.224 --> 00:07:06.484
Anybody else?

41
00:07:26.685 --> 00:07:29.562
- Mom. I'm home.
- I'm up here. honey.

42
00:07:31.577 --> 00:07:32.962
- Hi
- Hey. Mom.

43
00:07:32.963 --> 00:07:35.257
- How was school today?
- The usual.

44
00:07:36.363 --> 00:07:39.511
This dyslexia thing
is getting worse.

45
00:07:40.785 --> 00:07:42.297
Why do you think that?

46
00:07:43.648 --> 00:07:46.546
I don't know. maybe it's the ADHD.

47
00:07:48.648 --> 00:07:51.206
I thought this school was
suppose to make things better.

48
00:07:51.575 --> 00:07:53.309
Percy. I know how hard
this is for you.

49
00:07:54.655 --> 00:07:56.117
But someday. it will
all make sense.

50
00:07:56.974 --> 00:07:58.306
Really?

51
00:07:58.541 --> 00:07:59.829
When?

52
00:08:00.998 --> 00:08:02.939
Tonight? Tomorrow? When?

53
00:08:04.954 --> 00:08:06.224
Woman.

54
00:08:07.173 --> 00:08:08.509
Hi. Gabe.

55
00:08:09.188 --> 00:08:10.467
Where's my beer?

56
00:08:11.165 --> 00:08:12.424
It's in the fridge.

57
00:08:12.869 --> 00:08:16.649
So what. it's suppose to magically
float from the ice box and into my hand.

58
00:08:20.504 --> 00:08:22.296
Oh come on. man.
You could do that right here?

59
00:08:22.529 --> 00:08:24.515
It's disgusting. we're in the kitchen.

60
00:08:27.499 --> 00:08:28.894
Yeah. real charming
you got that.

61
00:08:29.951 --> 00:08:31.539
Show some respect.

62
00:08:31.966 --> 00:08:33.273
That's my mom. right there.

63
00:08:41.906 --> 00:08:43.534
This is my house.

64
00:08:45.201 --> 00:08:47.263
You show some respect.

65
00:08:50.829 --> 00:08:54.375
Why do you stay with that pig?
He smells like a sewer.

66
00:08:54.550 --> 00:08:57.427
He sleeps till noon everyday.
and he can't even hold a job.

67
00:08:57.495 --> 00:08:58.841
Why do you stay with him?

68
00:09:01.933 --> 00:09:05.227
He's been good to us. Percy
in ways you don't understand.

69
00:09:07.106 --> 00:09:10.071
You're right. I don't understand.
I don't get it.

70
00:09:37.343 --> 00:09:41.279
Be prepared. everything
is about to change. Percy.

71
00:09:41.791 --> 00:09:44.620
Everything is about to change ...

72
00:09:53.495 --> 00:09:55.751
There are 12 Olympian gods.

73
00:09:56.295 --> 00:10:00.751
The big three are the brothers
Zeus. Poseidon and Hades.

74
00:10:01.905 --> 00:10:06.478
They attained the power by
overthrowing their father. Kronos.

75
00:10:06.983 --> 00:10:09.981
chopping him into little pieces.

76
00:10:10.829 --> 00:10:13.041
The three gods have been rivals ever since.

77
00:10:14.037 --> 00:10:18.014
Always arguing. always
threatening war.

78
00:10:19.070 --> 00:10:21.631
On several occasions.
they would come down to Earth

79
00:10:22.220 --> 00:10:25.113
And. uhmm. how shall I put this?

80
00:10:25.332 --> 00:10:27.217
Hook up?

81
00:10:28.552 --> 00:10:30.696
They would hook up with mortals.

82
00:10:31.117 --> 00:10:35.470
The children produced
were half god. half human.

83
00:10:36.499 --> 00:10:38.763
Can anyone what
they were called?

84
00:10:39.496 --> 00:10:40.818
Percy?

85
00:10:43.945 --> 00:10:45.760
I'm sorry. what. Mr. Brunner?

86
00:10:47.891 --> 00:10:52.507
What is the proper name of the
offspring of a human and a god?

87
00:10:54.375 --> 00:10:56.773
- Demigod.
- Exactly.

88
00:10:57.438 --> 00:11:02.924
Many have been great heroes.
Like Hercules and Achilles.

89
00:11:03.346 --> 00:11:06.861
Can you name another?

90
00:11:09.623 --> 00:11:10.947
I'll give you a hint.

91
00:11:11.796 --> 00:11:13.532
You have something in common.

92
00:11:23.800 --> 00:11:28.433
Percy ... Perseus?

93
00:11:31.639 --> 00:11:32.950
Correct.

94
00:11:34.967 --> 00:11:37.725
Now over here. we have
a depiction of Hercules

95
00:11:37.726 --> 00:11:39.527
defeating the Nemean lion.

96
00:11:40.781 --> 00:11:44.418
Hercules killed the beast
with his bare hands

97
00:11:44.419 --> 00:11:46.504
and he took the skin as trophy.

98
00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:50.467
- Percy ...
- Yes. Ms. Dodds?

99
00:11:51.029 --> 00:11:52.503
We need to talk.

100
00:12:08.642 --> 00:12:10.062
So did I do something wrong?

101
00:12:12.575 --> 00:12:13.880
Ms. Dodds?

102
00:12:14.892 --> 00:12:16.178
Hello?

103
00:12:16.942 --> 00:12:18.227
Where is it?

104
00:12:21.030 --> 00:12:23.526
How did you get up there?

105
00:12:32.420 --> 00:12:34.167
You stole the lightning bolt!

106
00:12:34.168 --> 00:12:36.964
- I don't know what you're talking about!
- Give it to me!

107
00:12:38.883 --> 00:12:42.154
Give it to me now!

108
00:12:44.257 --> 00:12:45.523
Percy!

109
00:12:46.724 --> 00:12:48.028
Release him!

110
00:12:48.292 --> 00:12:49.552
You ...

111
00:12:49.553 --> 00:12:53.419
Release him or I swear
I'll tear you to pieces.

112
00:13:05.697 --> 00:13:08.446
I'm going crazy.
I should be on vacation.

113
00:13:08.447 --> 00:13:10.290
Percy. calm down.
Everything's gonna be okay.

114
00:13:10.742 --> 00:13:14.647
Oh God. wait.
Did that really just happen?

115
00:13:15.267 --> 00:13:16.576
She's turned to that thing?

116
00:13:16.754 --> 00:13:18.014
A fury.

117
00:13:18.419 --> 00:13:20.915
Concealed in our school.
I should have known.

118
00:13:20.916 --> 00:13:23.451
Wait. wait. A fury? What is a fury?

119
00:13:23.566 --> 00:13:25.380
And why did you say
you could tear her to pieces?

120
00:13:25.467 --> 00:13:26.766
What did she want from you?

121
00:13:27.498 --> 00:13:29.658
She ... said something ...

122
00:13:30.714 --> 00:13:32.040
about me ...

123
00:13:32.694 --> 00:13:34.322
stealing a lightning bolt.

124
00:13:35.209 --> 00:13:36.531
They've found him.

125
00:13:39.881 --> 00:13:41.728
- He's in danger.
- Who found me?

126
00:13:42.548 --> 00:13:44.276
- He's no longer safe here.
- Okay. where should we move him?

127
00:13:44.277 --> 00:13:45.845
We have no choice. the camp.

128
00:13:46.286 --> 00:13:48.368
What camp? Look. I'm standing right here.

129
00:13:48.369 --> 00:13:50.045
If they think he's the thief.

130
00:13:50.255 --> 00:13:52.389
there's nowhere safe from
heaven and earth for him now

131
00:13:52.390 --> 00:13:53.709
Percy.

132
00:13:53.910 --> 00:13:57.337
Take this to defend yourself.
It's a powerful weapon.

133
00:13:57.908 --> 00:14:02.806
Guard it well.
Only use it in times of severe distress.

134
00:14:04.737 --> 00:14:06.082
This is a pen.

135
00:14:06.303 --> 00:14:07.905
This is a pen!

136
00:14:07.906 --> 00:14:11.080
Take him to his mother.
And don't let him out of your sight.

137
00:14:11.346 --> 00:14:14.221
Percy. come on.
Come on. man. come on!

138
00:14:19.471 --> 00:14:20.813
What's going on?

139
00:14:21.570 --> 00:14:22.886
Don't trust anyone. okay.

140
00:14:23.243 --> 00:14:25.105
Don't look at anybody.
just keep walking.

141
00:14:25.106 --> 00:14:27.433
Why did Mr. Brunner
ask you to watch me?

142
00:14:27.434 --> 00:14:29.059
- Because I'm your protector.
- Wait. hang on.

143
00:14:29.060 --> 00:14:30.611
My protector? Are you kidding?

144
00:14:31.544 --> 00:14:34.280
What? You think because I'm
like this I'm not capable of keeping you safe?

145
00:14:34.314 --> 00:14:36.051
Maybe you're not seeing
what I'm seeing.

146
00:14:36.052 --> 00:14:37.634
You have crutches.

147
00:14:37.635 --> 00:14:39.242
Look. I will give my life
to secure your well-being.

148
00:14:39.243 --> 00:14:41.188
What are you talking about?
What's going on?

149
00:14:41.423 --> 00:14:42.691
We gotta warn your mom.

150
00:14:43.139 --> 00:14:45.771
Come on. Percy. Come on.

151
00:14:46.651 --> 00:14:49.718
Sally! More beer!

152
00:14:51.438 --> 00:14:52.940
Look. we gotta talk. okay.

153
00:14:54.313 --> 00:14:56.711
Can't you see she's servicing
me and my friends?

154
00:14:57.409 --> 00:15:00.064
Hey. hey. don't talk about my mom
like that. you bald-headed freak.

155
00:15:07.737 --> 00:15:10.793
- Nice one.
- Like I said. I'm your protector.

156
00:15:13.095 --> 00:15:16.400
Sally. Percy has to leave now.
Like right now.

157
00:15:23.553 --> 00:15:24.907
What is happening?

158
00:15:25.095 --> 00:15:29.342
- Okay. I swear I didn't steal anything.
- Honey. I believe you. I believe you.

159
00:15:30.998 --> 00:15:33.065
Where are you taking me?
What is this camp?

160
00:15:33.066 --> 00:15:36.539
It's a camp for really special
people like you.

161
00:15:36.540 --> 00:15:39.881
Special people. what. am I
crazy or something?

162
00:15:40.224 --> 00:15:41.792
No. honey. no.

163
00:15:42.655 --> 00:15:44.446
Percy. this is about your father.

164
00:15:55.176 --> 00:15:57.632
Your father was unlike
any guy you've ever seen...

165
00:15:57.633 --> 00:15:59.985
he was just dazzling.

166
00:16:00.302 --> 00:16:01.984
Now he's dazzling?

167
00:16:05.303 --> 00:16:08.444
And then you came along
and then it was just perfect.

168
00:16:09.465 --> 00:16:11.221
But he had to leave.

169
00:16:12.188 --> 00:16:14.247
So he did abandon us.

170
00:16:14.840 --> 00:16:17.536
No. honey.
He was forced to. He loved you.

171
00:16:18.688 --> 00:16:22.144
Leaving you. it was probably the
most difficult thing he ever did.

172
00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:34.487
Why did he had to go?

173
00:16:35.550 --> 00:16:38.055
- Because he's ...
- Sally. watch out!

174
00:16:47.918 --> 00:16:50.302
- Percy!
- Mom. are you alright?

175
00:16:50.986 --> 00:16:52.270
Grover. are you alright?

176
00:16:54.133 --> 00:16:56.305
Is it me or is it raining cows?

177
00:17:00.856 --> 00:17:02.748
What is that?

178
00:17:02.749 --> 00:17:05.513
Get out! Come on!

179
00:17:05.936 --> 00:17:08.147
Why are you taking your pants off?
What are you doing?

180
00:17:08.148 --> 00:17:09.528
My job.

181
00:17:09.563 --> 00:17:11.246
Whoa. whoa.
You're half doggie?

182
00:17:11.531 --> 00:17:13.075
I'm half goat.

183
00:17:19.523 --> 00:17:21.435
Watch out.
There's glass.

184
00:17:22.316 --> 00:17:24.695
Come on. get out of the
car. that thing's getting closer!

185
00:17:25.142 --> 00:17:27.821
- Do you ever need these?
- It's just for show.

186
00:17:28.843 --> 00:17:30.167
Follow me!

187
00:17:34.584 --> 00:17:36.616
This way. guys. This way.

188
00:17:36.617 --> 00:17:39.973
Come on! Come on!
Run! Run!

189
00:17:39.974 --> 00:17:41.660
Go. go!

190
00:17:54.278 --> 00:17:55.959
Come on!

191
00:18:00.503 --> 00:18:01.784
We're here.

192
00:18:08.625 --> 00:18:10.193
Grover!

193
00:18:12.391 --> 00:18:14.152
Mom. what are you doing?

194
00:18:14.153 --> 00:18:15.495
This is as far as I can get.

195
00:18:15.775 --> 00:18:18.325
I can't go through.
I'm not like you.

196
00:18:18.752 --> 00:18:21.280
- I'm not leaving without you.
- You have to!

197
00:18:21.889 --> 00:18:23.171
You have to.

198
00:18:30.082 --> 00:18:31.932
Put my mother down!

199
00:18:31.966 --> 00:18:34.921
Percy. go!
You're safe inside the gate.

200
00:18:34.922 --> 00:18:36.904
- What can I do?
- Use the pen!

201
00:18:36.905 --> 00:18:38.877
- What?
- Use Brunner's pen and click it.

202
00:19:01.726 --> 00:19:03.381
Are you okay?

203
00:19:14.639 --> 00:19:16.150
Percy. behind you!

204
00:19:29.964 --> 00:19:31.861
- Percy. are you okay?
- I'm not feeling...

205
00:19:31.992 --> 00:19:33.264
Percy!

206
00:19:58.315 --> 00:20:01.330
- It hurts.
- I'm sure glad you're alive.

207
00:20:14.201 --> 00:20:16.512
Where am I? What is this place?

208
00:20:16.695 --> 00:20:19.386
The infirmary. You've been
unconscious for three days.

209
00:20:19.663 --> 00:20:21.118
Three days?

210
00:20:21.935 --> 00:20:24.024
So. Percy.

211
00:20:24.888 --> 00:20:26.246
What do you remember?

212
00:20:27.201 --> 00:20:29.700
Some crazy dream.

213
00:20:29.701 --> 00:20:31.774
There was a monster.

214
00:20:32.079 --> 00:20:34.384
My mom was there.
you were there too.

215
00:20:34.385 --> 00:20:37.532
You were some weird hybrid
man-goat thing. whoa.

216
00:20:41.873 --> 00:20:44.091
Put it in the correct term. it's satyr.

217
00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:51.954
All of it was real?

218
00:20:52.229 --> 00:20:53.642
My mom was gone?

219
00:20:55.143 --> 00:20:58.237
I'm sorry. Percy.
I tried. man. I really do.

220
00:20:59.848 --> 00:21:01.841
But frankly. I'm just
a junior protector.

221
00:21:02.217 --> 00:21:03.550
I don't have horns yet.

222
00:21:04.442 --> 00:21:06.119
It's my fault.

223
00:21:06.154 --> 00:21:07.899
It was my job to protect you.

224
00:21:08.399 --> 00:21:09.989
Both of you.

225
00:21:20.384 --> 00:21:22.970
So. this is Camp Half-Blood.

226
00:21:22.971 --> 00:21:25.691
- What do you mean. what?
- I think you know.

227
00:21:26.323 --> 00:21:27.959
Half mean. half mortal. half god.

228
00:21:28.121 --> 00:21:30.727
- Fire!
- Oh guys. watch the arrows!

229
00:21:31.453 --> 00:21:34.218
Newcomer. hello.

230
00:21:34.809 --> 00:21:37.502
Look. man. Remember all the myths
about great gods and goddesses.

231
00:21:37.503 --> 00:21:40.198
Well. they're not myths.

232
00:21:41.158 --> 00:21:42.800
Remember what Mr. Brunner said.
Sometimes...

233
00:21:42.810 --> 00:21:45.075
they come down to Earth
and they fall in love with mortals.

234
00:21:45.364 --> 00:21:47.392
And they'll have kids.

235
00:21:48.110 --> 00:21:49.871
- No way.
- Yes way.

236
00:21:50.782 --> 00:21:52.854
Yup. you're a demigod.

237
00:21:53.208 --> 00:21:54.910
Two points for Percy Jackson!

238
00:21:57.063 --> 00:21:59.406
Don't worry. but you're not alone.
There's hundreds in the world.

239
00:21:59.886 --> 00:22:01.192
Some live normal lives.

240
00:22:01.558 --> 00:22:04.124
And some. I'm not allowed to
vulgar names are very famous.

241
00:22:04.473 --> 00:22:06.100
I'm talking about like
White House famous.

242
00:22:07.503 --> 00:22:10.798
See man. this place right here. This is the place
where you learn to harness your powers.

243
00:22:11.466 --> 00:22:14.655
You train to become leaders.
warriors and heroes.

244
00:22:15.189 --> 00:22:17.022
I think you have the wrong guy.

245
00:22:17.378 --> 00:22:19.337
I'm not a hero. I'm a loser.

246
00:22:19.365 --> 00:22:21.066
I have dyslexia and ADHD.

247
00:22:21.617 --> 00:22:23.098
And those are your
greatest gifts.

248
00:22:24.350 --> 00:22:26.497
If you kinda read.
the words float off the page. right?

249
00:22:26.993 --> 00:22:30.095
That's because your brain's hotwired
for ancient Greek and not English.

250
00:22:30.255 --> 00:22:33.580
- Right. At the museum I can read.
- Yeah.

251
00:22:33.589 --> 00:22:35.127
And your ADHD...

252
00:22:36.655 --> 00:22:39.462
You're impulsive. Percy.
You can't be still!

253
00:22:40.339 --> 00:22:42.278
Those are your natural battle reflexes. man.

254
00:22:42.846 --> 00:22:44.475
They kept you alive
in your fight.

255
00:22:45.314 --> 00:22:48.469
Look. no pitiful loser
can defeat a Minotaur.

256
00:22:49.714 --> 00:22:53.015
Your blood is special.
It's the blood of a god.

257
00:22:54.411 --> 00:22:56.173
That's a lot to process.

258
00:22:56.482 --> 00:22:58.806
A lot. A lot.

259
00:23:03.198 --> 00:23:05.281
This is where you'll do most
of your battle training.

260
00:23:19.578 --> 00:23:20.873
What's her name?

261
00:23:22.903 --> 00:23:26.256
- She will squash you like a bug.
- Her name?

262
00:23:26.729 --> 00:23:29.825
Annabeth. Daughter of
Athena. the goddess of wisdom.

263
00:23:35.107 --> 00:23:36.836
Hey. no staring.
Keep it moving.

264
00:23:37.183 --> 00:23:38.451
Come on. come on.

265
00:23:41.949 --> 00:23:44.839
There's someone I want
you to see. Check this out.

266
00:23:58.228 --> 00:24:00.939
- What are those things?
- The centaurs.

267
00:24:03.558 --> 00:24:06.694
- Wait. is that Mr. Brunner?
- Come on.

268
00:24:14.044 --> 00:24:15.342
Mr. Brunner?

269
00:24:15.998 --> 00:24:18.856
In my world. I'm
known as Chiron.

270
00:24:20.220 --> 00:24:22.829
- Are you recovered?
- Am I recovered?

271
00:24:22.941 --> 00:24:25.367
You. you're not in a wheelchair.

272
00:24:25.406 --> 00:24:29.233
- You have ...
- A real horse's ass.

273
00:24:30.361 --> 00:24:32.048
I apologize for hiding
my true form.

274
00:24:32.058 --> 00:24:33.556
but I needed to keep an eye on you.

275
00:24:34.580 --> 00:24:37.440
I hope you'll forgive me. Come.

276
00:24:50.324 --> 00:24:53.599
Grover! Grover. come here!

277
00:24:54.913 --> 00:24:56.236
Daughters of Aphrodite.

278
00:24:57.006 --> 00:24:59.529
Alright. guys. You guys
got a lot of catching up to do.

279
00:24:59.738 --> 00:25:02.152
Their mother is the goddess of love.
Let's see where that leads.

280
00:25:02.775 --> 00:25:06.401
- Hey. baby!
- Satyrs ...

281
00:25:09.124 --> 00:25:10.471
What is this place?

282
00:25:11.951 --> 00:25:15.164
Welcome home.
His father built this.

283
00:25:15.675 --> 00:25:16.950
For you.

284
00:25:28.164 --> 00:25:29.433
This whole place is mine?

285
00:25:44.924 --> 00:25:46.337
I think it has some weight to it.

286
00:25:53.040 --> 00:25:56.761
- My father is Poseidon.
- God of the seas.

287
00:25:57.560 --> 00:25:58.958
Why didn't anybody tell me?

288
00:25:59.962 --> 00:26:01.305
It was for your own safety.

289
00:26:03.227 --> 00:26:07.045
It's extremely rare for a child
to be born to one of the big three.

290
00:26:09.346 --> 00:26:12.556
They're very powerful.
A threat.

291
00:26:13.206 --> 00:26:15.387
A threat?
Who am I threatening?

292
00:26:17.048 --> 00:26:21.108
Poseidon's brothers.
Zeus and Hades.

293
00:26:23.236 --> 00:26:25.768
That's why your mother
married your stepfather.

294
00:26:26.333 --> 00:26:29.347
His pungent odor masked
the smell of your blood.

295
00:26:30.564 --> 00:26:34.208
And hid you from
anything or anyone

296
00:26:34.315 --> 00:26:35.901
that gods have sent to kill you.

297
00:26:37.863 --> 00:26:40.022
My mother put up with
that creep to protect me?

298
00:26:45.290 --> 00:26:46.599
I wish I've known...

299
00:26:47.708 --> 00:26:50.046
She sacrificed so much for me.

300
00:26:53.817 --> 00:26:55.207
Now she's gone.

301
00:27:02.666 --> 00:27:06.279
- Why am I even here?
- You're here because you're in jeopardy.

302
00:27:07.064 --> 00:27:08.776
Everyone thinks you're
the lightning thief.

303
00:27:09.651 --> 00:27:11.002
Look. I didn't steal it.

304
00:27:15.229 --> 00:27:18.504
Zeus' bolt is the most powerful
weapon ever created.

305
00:27:20.071 --> 00:27:21.968
And if it's not returned by
summer solstice

306
00:27:21.978 --> 00:27:25.945
- In ten days. there will be a war.
- This is your problem. alright. not mine.

307
00:27:26.207 --> 00:27:27.772
This is about your world not mine.

308
00:27:27.781 --> 00:27:29.698
This is about all worlds.

309
00:27:31.598 --> 00:27:33.432
The Olympians would be
forced to choose sides.

310
00:27:33.497 --> 00:27:35.126
Earth would become
a battleground.

311
00:27:35.442 --> 00:27:38.491
Mountains erupting.
earthquakes. raging fires!

312
00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:41.407
The end of life as you know it.

313
00:27:46.804 --> 00:27:48.072
What can we do?

314
00:27:48.453 --> 00:27:52.332
I want to take you to Olympus.
Convince Zeus of your innocence.

315
00:27:53.212 --> 00:27:55.556
Someone's using you
to start a war.

316
00:27:57.680 --> 00:27:59.211
What are we doing here? Let's go now.

317
00:27:59.465 --> 00:28:02.482
Your boldness is commendable.
but outside those gates.

318
00:28:02.578 --> 00:28:06.083
you will be in danger
at all times.

319
00:28:07.017 --> 00:28:09.708
The Fury and the Minotaur
were only the beginning.

320
00:28:10.739 --> 00:28:15.169
First. you must train.

321
00:28:20.276 --> 00:28:22.257
This is always a fun
game to watch.

322
00:28:23.560 --> 00:28:25.957
How do you guys wear these stuff?
It weighs more than me!

323
00:28:26.138 --> 00:28:29.004
- Trust me. wear it or you'll get killed.
- Wait. what?

324
00:28:29.948 --> 00:28:31.355
- Wait.
- Heroes!

325
00:28:32.393 --> 00:28:35.588
Warriors! Come on!

326
00:28:40.869 --> 00:28:42.256
Hustle. hassle.

327
00:28:42.918 --> 00:28:45.699
Stop bloody gagging.

328
00:28:47.771 --> 00:28:50.881
Percy. step forward.

329
00:28:54.423 --> 00:28:57.849
This is Percy Jackson.

330
00:28:59.694 --> 00:29:01.247
He's gonna need a team.

331
00:29:02.180 --> 00:29:03.465
We'll take him.

332
00:29:07.392 --> 00:29:10.549
I'm Luke. son of Hermes
and camp leader.

333
00:29:11.205 --> 00:29:12.736
Not necessarily in that order.

334
00:29:13.397 --> 00:29:16.451
- Where's your helmet?
- No one gave me one.

335
00:29:18.871 --> 00:29:22.418
Chiron. you still got your wheelchair?
He's gonna need it.

336
00:29:22.970 --> 00:29:24.309
You're gone here. man.

337
00:29:25.654 --> 00:29:28.650
I'm messing with you.
Smile a little bit. It's good for you. kid.

338
00:29:29.159 --> 00:29:31.845
Anybody got an extra helmet?
Please pass it up.

339
00:29:35.994 --> 00:29:37.272
Try it on.

340
00:29:38.533 --> 00:29:40.912
That will protect you.
From all of us.

341
00:29:41.584 --> 00:29:43.295
Welcome to the
blue soldiers. my friend.

342
00:29:44.291 --> 00:29:47.664
Alright. everyone in position
for capture the flag.

343
00:29:48.208 --> 00:29:51.383
First team to capture
the enemy's banner wins.

344
00:29:51.916 --> 00:29:53.255
Dismissed.

345
00:29:54.757 --> 00:29:58.508
Ready. steady. now!

346
00:30:17.012 --> 00:30:18.634
Percy I know where
the flag is at. come on!

347
00:30:24.005 --> 00:30:26.757
Keep your eyes open and don't get killed.

348
00:30:40.108 --> 00:30:41.402
I'm coming. buddy.
I'm coming.

349
00:30:41.665 --> 00:30:42.997
Sons of Ares. Watch out!

350
00:30:42.998 --> 00:30:44.515
Well. that's a sword!
That's a sword!

351
00:30:48.525 --> 00:30:50.504
You guys take camp
way too seriously.

352
00:30:51.524 --> 00:30:52.860
Go!

353
00:31:05.257 --> 00:31:08.631
Percy. get out here!
Go look for the flag.

354
00:31:08.906 --> 00:31:10.546
How did I just do that?

355
00:31:41.347 --> 00:31:42.701
I won.

356
00:31:44.915 --> 00:31:47.054
Do you really think it
would be that easy?

357
00:31:52.441 --> 00:31:55.075
My mother is goddess of
wisdom and battle strategy.

358
00:31:55.543 --> 00:31:59.955
Do you know what that means?
I always win.

359
00:32:00.845 --> 00:32:04.002
I always lose.
Maybe we're both wrong.

360
00:32:22.485 --> 00:32:23.913
Hey Chiron. shouldn't we
get there and stop it.

361
00:32:24.139 --> 00:32:25.829
- Coz she's killing him. man.
- You gotta be kidding.

362
00:32:26.590 --> 00:32:27.967
This is the best part.

363
00:32:34.705 --> 00:32:36.591
- God!
- Stand up and fight.

364
00:32:38.456 --> 00:32:39.815
Hero.

365
00:32:54.474 --> 00:32:55.973
Come on. Percy.

366
00:33:03.409 --> 00:33:04.890
Go to the water.

367
00:33:11.945 --> 00:33:14.107
The water will give you power.

368
00:35:57.414 --> 00:35:58.818
Excuse me. Excuse me!

369
00:35:58.852 --> 00:36:01.418
Ladies and gentlemen. the son
of Poseidon is coming through!

370
00:36:01.452 --> 00:36:03.796
A hero is coming through! Move it!

371
00:36:04.218 --> 00:36:06.139
Hey. no dirty look. Stop that.

372
00:36:06.987 --> 00:36:08.268
Hey. Percy?

373
00:36:09.105 --> 00:36:11.330
We're having a party
at our place later

374
00:36:11.364 --> 00:36:13.276
and we would really
love it if you came.

375
00:36:13.310 --> 00:36:14.919
I would love to come.
that'll be great.

376
00:36:14.952 --> 00:36:16.495
- That will be amazing!
- Really grand.

377
00:36:16.529 --> 00:36:18.997
I would love to come too.
to the party. you know.

378
00:36:19.031 --> 00:36:20.475
Thanks for inviting me. ladies.

379
00:36:20.509 --> 00:36:21.874
Beat it. nymphs.

380
00:36:22.097 --> 00:36:24.634
Wait. don't leave. ladies.
I'm available.

381
00:36:24.896 --> 00:36:27.317
Hey. come on. don't leave.
I'm available! What time's the party?

382
00:36:28.405 --> 00:36:30.163
Feeling like a hero?

383
00:36:30.197 --> 00:36:31.494
More like a mutant.

384
00:36:31.971 --> 00:36:34.653
I'm not gonna grow a fish tail
or gills or anything like that. am I?

385
00:36:34.687 --> 00:36:36.060
Not likely.

386
00:36:36.625 --> 00:36:38.793
Although a huge ego is
not out of question.

387
00:36:42.398 --> 00:36:44.197
You know. you could've
killed me out there.

388
00:36:44.507 --> 00:36:46.869
I could've died if
I was normal.

389
00:36:46.902 --> 00:36:48.267
But you aren't.

390
00:36:49.696 --> 00:36:51.892
I get a sense that
you don't like me very much.

391
00:36:52.214 --> 00:36:53.496
It's possible.

392
00:36:54.001 --> 00:36:55.749
I mean. our parents
hate each other.

393
00:36:55.784 --> 00:36:57.200
Wait. they do?

394
00:36:58.492 --> 00:37:00.727
I definitely have strong
feelings for you.

395
00:37:01.845 --> 00:37:04.760
I just haven't decided if
they're positive or negative.

396
00:37:05.983 --> 00:37:09.190
Well. you let me know
when you figured it out.

397
00:37:09.958 --> 00:37:11.717
You'll be the first.

398
00:37:32.009 --> 00:37:34.652
Percy Jackson show me yourself!

399
00:37:54.136 --> 00:37:55.856
Hades. stay back!

400
00:37:58.178 --> 00:38:02.065
Percy Jackson. bring
me the bolt.

401
00:38:04.816 --> 00:38:08.304
Be a good boy. hand it to me.

402
00:38:08.337 --> 00:38:11.073
and I will exchange it for your mother.

403
00:38:12.464 --> 00:38:15.311
Percy. listen. Percy!

404
00:38:18.517 --> 00:38:20.307
My mother is gone!

405
00:38:21.549 --> 00:38:24.951
No. your mother is still alive.

406
00:38:25.350 --> 00:38:27.915
I sent the minotaur
to abduct her.

407
00:38:28.236 --> 00:38:30.821
She's here with me
in the Underworld.

408
00:38:37.644 --> 00:38:38.916
Mom?

409
00:38:39.966 --> 00:38:41.306
Percy.

410
00:38:46.487 --> 00:38:48.192
What have you done with my mother?

411
00:38:48.226 --> 00:38:52.366
If you ever want to see your mother
again. you will bring me the bolt.

412
00:38:58.673 --> 00:39:00.819
Chiron. I have to go get her.

413
00:39:00.854 --> 00:39:02.967
Percy. you don't have the bolt.

414
00:39:03.002 --> 00:39:04.386
I'm gonna tell him the truth.

415
00:39:04.726 --> 00:39:07.000
When he realizes. I'm not the thief.

416
00:39:07.034 --> 00:39:08.546
- He'll release her.
- No.

417
00:39:08.838 --> 00:39:10.475
You cannot negotiate with Hades.

418
00:39:10.509 --> 00:39:12.746
When he finds out you
don't have the bolt

419
00:39:13.910 --> 00:39:15.630
he will kill you and your mother.

420
00:39:15.664 --> 00:39:17.536
But this is our only chance.

421
00:39:17.537 --> 00:39:20.120
No. stick to our plan.

422
00:39:20.927 --> 00:39:22.700
Come to Olympus.

423
00:39:22.734 --> 00:39:24.439
Bargain with Zeus.

424
00:39:24.474 --> 00:39:26.430
Once you convince
him of your innocence.

425
00:39:26.431 --> 00:39:29.490
we will do everything in our
power to bring back your mother.

426
00:39:32.263 --> 00:39:33.596
Okay.

427
00:39:49.389 --> 00:39:50.800
Going somewhere?

428
00:39:52.403 --> 00:39:53.923
Yeah. I'll be going for a walk.

429
00:39:53.957 --> 00:39:55.444
For a walk?
I'm coming with you.

430
00:39:55.478 --> 00:39:57.217
No. I'm going alone.

431
00:39:57.252 --> 00:39:58.592
- No. I'm coming with you.
- No.

432
00:39:59.224 --> 00:40:00.654
You're being followed.

433
00:40:07.602 --> 00:40:09.701
Leave me alone.
Go to sleep or something.

434
00:40:09.734 --> 00:40:11.042
No.

435
00:40:11.848 --> 00:40:14.219
One small victory and you're
ready to fight Hades?

436
00:40:14.254 --> 00:40:15.804
- Double team.
- Really? You too?

437
00:40:17.009 --> 00:40:20.050
Look. I just found out my mother is
still alive. I'm gonna get her back.

438
00:40:20.085 --> 00:40:22.032
- From the Underworld?
- Whatever it takes.

439
00:40:22.402 --> 00:40:24.045
Yeah. well maybe you'll outsmart Hades.

440
00:40:24.079 --> 00:40:25.399
Maybe I will.

441
00:40:25.433 --> 00:40:26.775
I can't let you do this. okay?

442
00:40:26.808 --> 00:40:29.312
I'm not asking for your permission.

443
00:40:29.564 --> 00:40:30.832
Okay.

444
00:40:30.866 --> 00:40:33.636
Well. according to the regulations.
if I can't stop you

445
00:40:33.669 --> 00:40:35.987
I must accompany you. coz
I'm your best friend.

446
00:40:36.021 --> 00:40:38.379
- And your protector.
- Junior protector.

447
00:40:38.815 --> 00:40:40.103
Was that really necessary?

448
00:40:40.137 --> 00:40:43.713
I don't need your help. okay.
This is something I have to do on my own.

449
00:40:43.748 --> 00:40:45.667
Yeah well. we weren't
asking for you permission.

450
00:40:45.679 --> 00:40:46.945
Come on.

451
00:40:46.969 --> 00:40:49.933
Today you tried to kill me.
Now you wanna defend me?

452
00:40:49.967 --> 00:40:51.339
It wasn't real.

453
00:40:51.373 --> 00:40:52.711
That was just training.

454
00:40:53.092 --> 00:40:56.274
Percy. that's all I've ever done
is train and train.

455
00:40:56.308 --> 00:40:58.523
I've grown up here. I've only
been in the outside world

456
00:40:58.557 --> 00:40:59.898
a couple of times.

457
00:40:59.932 --> 00:41:02.635
And I've never had a chance
to go in an actual quest.

458
00:41:03.149 --> 00:41:05.850
Beside. you won one battle.

459
00:41:05.884 --> 00:41:07.554
and I've won hundreds.

460
00:41:07.588 --> 00:41:09.223
You're gonna need my experience.

461
00:41:09.582 --> 00:41:11.205
Good point.

462
00:41:12.644 --> 00:41:14.685
You two really wanna come.

463
00:41:14.718 --> 00:41:16.113
- Yeah.
- Yes.

464
00:41:16.959 --> 00:41:19.519
Okay. I guess we're all going.

465
00:41:19.553 --> 00:41:21.827
So. who knows how to
get to the Underworld?

466
00:41:23.576 --> 00:41:25.335
I did not think of that one.

467
00:41:27.434 --> 00:41:29.330
I think I know someone
who might.

468
00:41:35.082 --> 00:41:36.463
Luke?

469
00:41:38.436 --> 00:41:40.087
Hey. guys.

470
00:41:40.710 --> 00:41:44.042
Percy. I'm thinking that you'd
stop by sooner or later.

471
00:41:44.077 --> 00:41:46.024
Everybody does.

472
00:41:46.452 --> 00:41:49.446
Getting away from all
that Renaissance Fair...

473
00:41:49.479 --> 00:41:51.438
stuff out there. you know.

474
00:41:52.418 --> 00:41:53.887
But ...

475
00:41:55.392 --> 00:41:57.511
Welcome to the modern world.

476
00:41:58.765 --> 00:42:00.418
Cool stuff.

477
00:42:02.943 --> 00:42:04.799
What are you guys up to?

478
00:42:04.834 --> 00:42:06.655
We're going to get my mom back.

479
00:42:08.640 --> 00:42:10.878
You're dad is the messenger of the gods.

480
00:42:10.912 --> 00:42:13.750
One of the only ones who's gotten
in and out of the Underworld.

481
00:42:14.567 --> 00:42:16.402
Do you have any idea how?

482
00:42:18.073 --> 00:42:20.106
My dad's a jerk.
I've never met him.

483
00:42:20.572 --> 00:42:21.996
You too?

484
00:42:22.031 --> 00:42:23.906
Guess we all got
daddy issues. huh?

485
00:42:24.215 --> 00:42:25.702
That's because all gods are the same.

486
00:42:25.703 --> 00:42:29.066
Selfish. they only care
about themselves.

487
00:42:30.785 --> 00:42:33.059
But I once broke into
my dad's house.

488
00:42:33.093 --> 00:42:34.517
Got some cool stuff.

489
00:42:46.383 --> 00:42:47.753
For you.

490
00:42:58.646 --> 00:43:00.075
Flying shoes?

491
00:43:02.689 --> 00:43:04.060
My dad's.

492
00:43:04.817 --> 00:43:06.830
He has hundreds of these little guys.

493
00:43:09.977 --> 00:43:11.611
I won't even miss him.

494
00:43:11.853 --> 00:43:13.243
You're gonna need the other one.

495
00:43:18.578 --> 00:43:21.912
People have gone to the Underworld
before without having to be dead.

496
00:43:21.946 --> 00:43:25.099
Hercules did it. Morpheus did it.
my dad does it all the time.

497
00:43:25.134 --> 00:43:26.917
Getting in is the easy part.

498
00:43:27.121 --> 00:43:29.103
Getting out. well. that's tricky.

499
00:43:30.230 --> 00:43:31.998
This is a map to Persephone's pearls.

500
00:43:32.504 --> 00:43:33.776
Persephone?

501
00:43:34.079 --> 00:43:35.415
You mean Hades' wife?

502
00:43:35.448 --> 00:43:38.316
Yeah. he forced her to marry him.
He keeps her prisoner.

503
00:43:38.821 --> 00:43:40.715
Needless to say she hates it there.

504
00:43:40.749 --> 00:43:42.533
It's hot. he's a weirdo.

505
00:43:42.824 --> 00:43:46.332
So she has secret visitors.

506
00:43:48.490 --> 00:43:50.477
She keeps pearls and
put them all over the world.

507
00:43:50.511 --> 00:43:53.369
These pearls. they provide a
quick escape from the Underworld.

508
00:43:54.311 --> 00:43:55.740
You could use them to get out.

509
00:43:56.274 --> 00:43:57.596
So how do the pearls work?

510
